<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
In memcpy(mem, buf, size); the identifier buf is declared as void * but is used only as a read-only source. Rule 8.13 requires pointers to be const-qualified when possible, so buf should be declared as const void * (and the API that produces it adjusted if necessary). As written, buf is not const-qualified even though it is only read here, so the rule is violated.
</scenario>

